🌐 Load Balancer ------------------
  👉 A service that distributes incoming traffic across multiple VMs to ensure:
    High availability
    Scalability
    Reliability

  🏗️ Basic Flow
    User → Load Balancer → Multiple VMs (MIG)

  🔍 How it works (Important)
    User hits single IP (Load Balancer IP)
    Load balancer checks:
    Which VMs are healthy
    Sends request to one of them
    Response returned to user

  🔥 Types of Load Balancer in GCP
    🌍 Global HTTP(S) Load Balancer (Most used)
      Works across regions
      Layer 7 (application level)
      Smart routing
      🧠 How it works
      “Smart routing based on request content”

      👉 Best for:
        Websites / APIs
  
    🌐 TCP/UDP Load Balancer
      Layer 4
      For non-HTTP traffic
      🧠 How it works
        “Just forward traffic — no understanding of content”

      👉 Good for:
        TCP apps
        Databases

    📍 Internal Load Balancer
      Private traffic inside VPC
