🚀 Day 13: Volumes (Persistent Storage in Kubernetes)
  🛠️ Step-by-Step Actions
    🔹 1. Tested emptyDir (Temporary Storage)
          volumes:
          - name: my-volume
            emptyDir: {}
      👉 Mounted inside pod at /data
      🔍 Tested
        kubectl exec -it volume-pod -- bash
        echo "hello" > /data/test.txt
      🔥 Deleted Pod
        kubectl delete pod volume-pod
        👉 File lost ❌
      🧠 Learning
        emptyDir = temporary storage (lifecycle = pod)

    🔹 2. Tried Creating Persistent Volume (PV)
          kind: PersistentVolume
      ❌ Faced Error
        GKE Warden rejected request (hostPath not allowed)
      🧠 GKE AUTOPILOT LIMITATION (VERY IMPORTANT)
        In Google Kubernetes Engine Autopilot:
          ❌ hostPath is NOT allowed
          ❌ Manual PV creation is restricted
          ✅ Only supported storage types allowed
          ✅ Uses dynamic provisioning
      🧠 Reason
        Autopilot manages nodes → no direct node access → hostPath blocked

    🔹 3. Used PVC (Correct Approach)
          kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
      🔹 Created PVC
        kubectl apply -f pvc.yaml
      🔍 Verified
        kubectl get pvc
      👉 Status:
        Bound
      👉 Storage auto-created by GCP ✅

    🔹 4. Used PVC in Pod
          volumes:
          - name: my-storage
            persistentVolumeClaim:
              claimName: my-pvc
        🔍 Tested Persistence
          kubectl exec -it pvc-pod -- bash
          echo "persistent data" > /data/test.txt
        🔥 Deleted Pod
          kubectl delete pod pvc-pod
          kubectl apply -f pvc-pod.yaml
        🔍 Verified
          kubectl exec -it pvc-pod -- cat /data/test.txt
        👉 Output:
          persistent data
        🧠 Learning
          Data persists across pod restart ✅

      🔥 Debugging Scenarios
        🚫 Scenario 1: PVC Pending
          kubectl get pvc
          👉 STATUS = Pending
        🧠 Reason:
          No storage class / PV

        🚫 Scenario 2: Pod Not Starting
          kubectl describe pod pvc-pod
          👉 Volume mount error
        
        🚫 Scenario 3: Data Not Persisting
          🧠 Reason:
          Using emptyDir instead of PVC

        🚫 Scenario 4: Autopilot Restriction
          ❌ Error:
          hostPath PV rejected
          ✅ Fix:
          Use PVC only
