  🧠 Key Concepts
    Helm = Kubernetes package manager
    Chart = app package
    Release = deployed instance
    Supports:
    install
    upgrade
    rollback
    uninstall

  🔄 Rollback Concept
    Rollback creates new revision
    Does NOT revert revision number
    helm history my-nginx

  🔥 Issues Faced + Fixes
    ❌ Issue 1: Release Name Already Exists
      cannot re-use a name that is still in use
      ✅ Fix:
      helm uninstall my-nginx
      # OR
      helm upgrade my-nginx ...
  
    ❌ Issue 2: No Service Visible
      kubectl get svc
      👉 Only default services
      🧠 Reason:
      Helm install failed / partial deployment
      ✅ Fix:
      helm list -A
      helm uninstall my-nginx
      helm install my-nginx bitnami/nginx --set service.type=LoadBalancer --debug
  
    ❌ Issue 3: Deployment Not Found
      🧠 Reason:
      Wrong namespace / failed install
      ✅ Fix:
      kubectl get all -A
      helm status my-nginx
  
    ❌ Issue 4: Changes Not Applied
      🧠 Reason:
      Used install instead of upgrade
      ✅ Fix:
      helm upgrade my-nginx ...

  🧠 SRE Debug Flow
    1. helm list -A
    2. helm status <release>
    3. kubectl get all -A
    4. check namespace
    5. reinstall with --debug
